24/09/2006
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Prosecutors have submitted to the court 30 indictments of money laundering in the past 30 days, Deputy Chief Prosecutor Hristo Manchev announced on Saturday (23 September).
He and Interior Minister Rumen Petkov were holding a working meeting with representatives of the local administration, police and judiciary in Plovdiv.
According to Petkov, most of the money laundering cases surfaced during a joint operation with the FBI.
(Monitor - 24/09/06;
bTV, Darik - 23/09/06)
